== Roasted Carrots ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} on a diagonal into ½-inch-thick pieces.
Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}. Halve, peel, and mince @shallot{1}.
Roughly chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{},
and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

== Garlic Couscous ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} (medium pot for 4 servings)
over medium-high heat. Add @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, half the garlic, 1 TBSP
shallot (2 TBSP for 4), and a pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until
garlic is fragrant and couscous is lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add half the @beef stock concentrate{1} and ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4).
Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer and cover. Cook until couscous is
tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

== Salmon Fillet ==

Pat @salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with
@Italian seasoning{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4 servings), a big pinch of @salt{},
and pepper.

> Be sure to measure the Italian Seasoning—we sent more!

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat.
Add salmon and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes} per side.
(TIP: Reduce heat if salmon is browning too quickly.) Turn off heat; transfer
to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan and allow to cool for
~{1%minute}.

> Swap in chicken or pork for salmon. Cook chicken until cooked through,
> 3-5 minutes per side, or cook pork until cooked through, 4-6 minutes per
> side.

== Creamy Tomato Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in same pan over medium heat. Add remaining
shallot and remaining garlic; cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @tomato paste{1%unit}, remaining beef stock concentrate{1}, and ½ cup
water (¾ cup for 4 servings). Bring to a simmer and cook until reduced,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @sour cream{3%tablespoon}. Season generously with
@pepper{}.

> If sauce is too thick, add water 1 tsp at a time until sauce reaches desired
> consistency.

== To Serve ==

Fluff couscous gently with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for
4 servings).

Thinly slice salmon crosswise.

> Thinly slice chicken crosswise or serve salmon whole! Salmon is fully cooked
> when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Divide couscous, salmon, and carrots between plates. Spoon sauce over salmon
and couscous. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.